# Flue Harness Spike — environment knobs (LAB ONLY)
# Copy to .env and fill in. Never commit a real .env.

# =============================================================================
# Two LLM endpoints. Flue binds models PER AGENT, so the harness agents run on a
# DIFFERENT model than the live voice brain — they never share the GPU on :11434.
# =============================================================================

# --- Voice brain: the LIVE local llama.cpp (LEAVE AS-IS; harness does NOT run here) ---
# This is the production voice brain on the Jetson (Gemma E4B). The spike reads it
# only for the connectivity sanity check / local-provider registration; the harness
# AGENTS are bound to HARNESS_LLM_* below, not to this endpoint.
LLM_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1
# llama.cpp ignores the model name and serves whatever .gguf it loaded; any
# non-empty string works. Set to your served model if your endpoint routes by name.
LLM_MODEL=local
# Most local llama.cpp servers need no key; placeholder keeps OpenAI clients happy.
LLM_API_KEY=not-needed

# --- Harness model: SEPARATE from the voice brain (what the agents actually run on) ---
# Default a CLOUD/DEV OpenAI-compatible endpoint for the build phase so the harness
# never competes with the voice brain for the live GPU slot on :11434.
# To go FULLY LOCAL later, point HARNESS_LLM_BASE_URL / HARNESS_LLM_MODEL at a local
# endpoint (a second llama.cpp, or :11434 once headroom allows) — NO code change.
HARNESS_LLM_PROVIDER=openai
HARNESS_LLM_BASE_URL=https://your-cloud-or-dev-endpoint.example/v1
HARNESS_LLM_MODEL=set-your-harness-model-here
# Real key for the cloud/dev endpoint (leave blank / "not-needed" for a local one).
HARNESS_LLM_API_KEY=

# --- GitHub target ---
# Token needs `repo` scope on GITHUB_REPO (push branch + open PR). If gh CLI is
# authenticated on the box you can leave this blank and let gh handle auth.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
GITHUB_REPO=jason-easyazz/zoe-ai-assistant
# The real Zoe issue the harness scouts + implements against.
TARGET_ISSUE=715

# --- Local checkout the spike branches from (must be a clone of GITHUB_REPO) ---
ZOE_CHECKOUT=/abs/path/to/zoe-ai-assistant

# --- Verify phase ---
# Command run during the verify phase to produce evidence. Keep it scoped/fast.
# Default is a no-op that always passes so the loop can be demonstrated end-to-end;
# replace with a real lint/test once the slice works.
VERIFY_CMD=echo "verify placeholder OK"
